{
  "text": "Hello everyone, welcome back to my channel. It's Winnie here from China Explore Tour. I'm going to do something super exciting today. So today we are about to do a traditional Hanfu furniture shop at China Explore Tour. Well I'm here at the city's Hanfu rental shop already. There are so many dresses here. I'm going to pick one. So Hanfu, it's basically traditional Chinese clothing that has been around for thousands of years. Every dynasty has its own unique style. So there's a lot to choose from. From super elegant to really royal. China Explore Tour offers professional Hanfu photo shoot services. So let's step into this Asian style and capture the beauty of traditional China. Oh look at this. Oh this is heavy. What I love this Hanfu piece is how detailed they are. Like look at embroidery and the patterns are based on traditional symbols from Asian China. This is also from the Qing dynasty but it's not for princess. I want to dress like a princess. This was worth thousands of yuan. The best one here. It's for queen. It doesn't suit for me. This is Ming dynasty. Oh by the way we also have Hanfu for guys. Look at this. Super cool right? Honestly I kind of want my boyfriend to wear this one. We could be like historical drama couple. What do you think? The red one or this one? I think this is suitable for the spring like the season right now. But this one is... this is noble. There's so many choices. I seriously can't decide. I will try them on after do the royal makeup. There's so many different parts and it's all for free. Look at these hair accessories. Like how extra it is. I love it. Time for hair and makeup. This is probably my favorite part. Start makeup and all styling. Gonna take you about 1 hour 50 minutes. We are starting with the hair first. It's all based on Asian hairstyles. Super intricate buns. Sometimes with adding volume using hair pieces. Honestly it's like Asian hairstyle magic. Then it's time for makeup. The look changes depends on the dynasty. Some go soft and elegant. Others fall and roll. The brows, lips and even forehead decorations all follow tradition. This is magic. This part takes time really. The stylish is recreating a traditional look from the dynasty. While the makeup sets, I'm heading over to try a few outfits. I still haven't picked the one yet and trust me it's not easy. I don't think there's a headband. It's a bit boring. I can't see it now. Try it. I'm gonna try this yellow one. I know. Sometimes customers they will change 20 clothes. So this job needs patience. Trying on hanbok is seriously the best part. Each color gives a total different vibe. This is my final choice. Oh look at this. Quick tip. When you pick hanbok, think about your skin tone and where you will shirt. Light colors pop on outdoor locations and darker tones are great if you want an extra dramatic. Now we have finished up the hair accessories. It's giving main character in historical drama. What I'm changing is qi tou. The qi tou of Qing dynasty is not just a headpiece. It represents Manchu culture and the status of women at the time. These headpieces will make from silk, beads and even gold. Red and gold are the most popular colors symbolizing nobility and wealth. Wow I'm outside. We are heading to the forbidden city. We're gonna take the photos in the exterior. Look at this. The patterns are super detailed and symbolic like flowers for beauty, character for nobility. The craftsmanship is seriously next level. Walking around Beijing like this definitely turns hot. But I kinda love it. It's like stepping out of a time machine. Like after we're having this photoshop, we can keep these clothes and then go to the forbidden city and take photos by ourselves. You need to return these clothes by 6 pm. So let's go. It's cool to see other people here in Tanfu too. The shoot itself was so fun. The photographer gave great directions. And I honestly feel like I was starring in my own Korean drama. I'm gonna change the location. A couple of tourists asked me what I'm wearing. I told them it's traditional Chinese outfit. And they look amazed. Do you wanna try it? So this is the Hanfu tour today. It's a magic day, right? And you just need to book with China Expo Tour. We're gonna arrange everything for you. Including hairstyle, food makeup, different clothes from different dynasties, including men, women, children, and elderly people. Everyone can choose his or her own costume. The perfect style and perfect colors match for you. Just visit our website. We are here for you. So that's all for today. If you like this video, just give me a like and subscribe our channel. Let's wait for the next adventure.",
